The paper proposes a deep learning approach for 3D human reconstruction from a single RGB image, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed method uses volumetric feature transformation and normal refinement, which are related to multimedia (MM) and machine learning (LG) subfields. Additionally, the paper introduces a new dataset for 3D human models, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
